      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2021-01-28</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-05-28T17:33:00Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><b>Protecting Tourism in the United States Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Commerce to study and report on the effects of the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) pandemic on the travel and tourism industry, including considerations of changes in industry employment rates and business revenues during the pandemic. </p> <p>In conducting this study, Commerce must consult with industry representatives and provide an opportunity for public comment and advice, and its report must include policy recommendations for promoting and assisting the travel and tourism industry.</p>]]>
          </text>
          <updateDate>2021-01-28T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <versionCode>25</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2021-12-16</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Reported to Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2022-02-28T21:50:49Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><b>Protecting Tourism in the United States Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Commerce to study and report on the effects of the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) pandemic on the travel and tourism industry, including considerations of changes in industry employment rates and business revenues during the pandemic. </p> <p>In conducting this study, Commerce must consult with industry representatives and provide an opportunity for public comment and advice, and its report must include policy recommendations for promoting and assisting the travel and tourism industry.</p>]]>
          </text>
          <updateDate>2021-12-16T14:30:33Z</updateDate>
          <name>Reported to Senate</name>
        </item>
